The paper deals with hyper-parameter optimization of deep convolutional networks for object recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses sequential model-based optimization (SMBO), which is a subfield of optimization and could place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
